During a press briefing aboard Air Force One, White House spokesperson Lindsay Walters provided updates on Hurricane Irma and the President's focus on tax reform. The President has been advocating for simplifying the tax code since his campaign days, and he is committed to boosting the economy and helping the middle class through tax reform. Walters also mentioned the President's trip to North Dakota, where he will address tax reform and bipartisan cooperation on the issue. Additionally, Walters announced that President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump have personally donated $1 million to Hurricane Harvey relief efforts, with the funds being distributed to various organizations. The briefing also touched on the resignation of Vice Chair of the Federal Reserve Stanley Fischer and the President's stance on the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals (DACA) program.